PROGRAM
Introductory Remarks:
LELAND CUTLER
President, Golden Gate International Exposition
Presiding Officer:
COLONEL CLARENCE M. YOUNG
Manager, Pacific Division, Pan American Airways
Speakers:
WILLIAM H. McCARTHY
Postmaster, San Francisco
GEORGE CREEL
Federal Commissioner, Golden Gate International Exposition
MAYOR ANGELO J. RossI
MARSHALL DILL
President, San Francisco Chamber of Commerce
ARTHUR J. DOLAN, JR.
President, San Francisco Junior Chamber of Commerce
Christening:
MRs. WALLACE M. ALEXAnDER
INSPECTION OF CLIPPER BY INVITED GUESTS
Music by the Golden Gate International Exposition Band
SPEAKERS' STAND
Mr. Wallace M. Alexander
Rear-Admiral Arthur J. Hepburn
Mrs. Wallace M. Alexander
Mr. A. J. Lundberg
Capt. J. A. Alger
Postmaster Wm. H. McCarthy
Major General A. J. Bowley
Mayor Wm. J. McCracken
Mr. L. E. Byington
Mr. A. J. McFadden
Mr. E. G. Cahill
Mr. W. W. Monahan
Mr. Horace Connick
Mr. L. J. O'Reilly
Mr. C. E. Cooley
Col. H. L. Parsons
Mr. George Creel
Mayor Angelo J. Rossi
Mr. Leland Cutler
Mr. W.P. Roth
Mr. Marshall Dill
Mr. C. H. Schwanenberg
Mr. Arthur Dolan, Jr.
Dr. Friench Simpson
Mr. C. O. Dunbar
Mr. Joseph R. Sheehan
Dr. Frank L. Gerbode
Mr. Sydney G. Walton
Mrs. Frank L. Gerbode
Mr. A. O. Willoughby
Mr. Edwin L. Haff
Col. Clarence M. Young
Mr. John M. Hassler
Mrs. Clarence M. Young
SPECIAL NOTICE
Those desiring to inspect the
ALTON TIER Ter the Chit ching coem ones should
proceed through Gate A, (located at the right of the spectators'
area.) At least one-half hour will be required to launch the ship
and moor it at the passenger dock for inspection. During this period
of unavoidable delay, the Traffic Area on the waterfront side of the
Hall of Air Transportation and the Traffic Terminal room will be
open to our guests.
Inspection of the CLIpper will be in limited groups of ten or
twelve persons who will be assembled by Pan American traffic
guides on the walkway leading to the CLIppER dock.
Due to the unprecedented interest which has been displayed in
this new aircraft, it is urgently requested that those who have
already seen the plane forego this occasion of inspection.
Pan American Airways Company
